		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				A small blue man form is seen trudging through the burning sands of the desert. As it trudges ever forward it becomes recognizeable as a half dead half fried young warrior of his 16th season. His name is Doledar Edgewalker. He has never felt quite so much like stripping off his armor chucking the 100 plus pounds of gear and running naked through the sands as a madman would. He has a mission . his mission is to prove hisself worthy to his mentor Master Daraden Bloodstorm. To do this and earn his entrance to the esteemed Order of the Shifting Sands Doledar has been ordered to Go to each of the prominate landmarks in the desert and check in with a guild member at each one the first one was quite easy as it was the inn in the lush green section of Northern Ro. then on to the palm. the next leg was to the platform,which in reality is just a buried wizard teleporter. then to the tunnel entrance. Not as hard as you think ehh?  <br> Well Doledar was ill prepared for the rigors of the desert he had studied maps and worked on his land navigation skills and his fighting technique but had slept through the survivl instruction back in freeport. He had been out of food for 3 days and was 2 swallows from being out of water and he would be damned if he would show weakness by asking for a handout from the guild he was seeking entance to at the next check point which was the monolith.  <br> Dole peered in to the blazing distance and thought he saw a man shape and waved franticly in greeting. the shape moved toward him as did an awefull stench as dole realized he had caught the atention of an dreaded mummy . Dole was too scared to move but his training took over and he moved up hill to make the creature come to him up hill and hopefully up wind. The mummy shambled toward the warrior and swung his mighty thews at the young warrior knocking him back and stunning him. As Doledar came out of his stunned state he loosed a bloodcurdleing battle screech and sliced into the horrid undead thing as a red tinge overtook his vision and the rage of battle consumed his very soul Doledar faded from existance and a wiled ravenous beast took the fore of his mind swing,slice kill ,survive screaming with all his soul the once human was becoming all armor and wrath. as the fight went on more hapless creatures were attracted by the blood and noise and the warrior slayed them all with out remorse or thought the berserkerbeast that was the essence of the true warrior had taken over. as the dust cleared severed limbs from undead mummies and orc raiders and scouts were all over the desert floor and Doledar was covered head to toe in gore and dust and entrails. As his battle rage subsided he realized that the tide of battle had swept him neared\r his goal and the monolith was in sight. He limped off toward the stone marker like a man over board clutching at a lifeline he fell to his knees and barely held his axe as he crawled the last 100 feet to the stone monilith and his waiting mentor Daraden was smileing down at him and said ...... Your are late Dole. Doledar almost fainted from laughing so hard as Daraden handed him a flask of water which Doledar drank greedily. The rest of the order gathered from the far flung reaches of the desert to welcome their newest leuitenant to the Order and heald all the wounds and a bit of ale put the zest back in the Exhausted warriors boddy as the party spilled into the barbarian fishing village and in to the warm firelight Doledar fell into the first peacefull sleep in weeks knowing that his new found brothers and sisters would watch his back as he would theirs as long as they all lived.  <br>  <br> Please comments welcome except on punctuation i was in a hurry and have not edited just a rough draft any way.  <br>  <br> Doledar Edgewalker  <br> Officer OSS  <br> Warrior 34th season 		

